Stat 290: Git details

Behind the scene

Behind the scene, all that is happening is that a series of git commands are being executed.

For example, you could set up a bare repository on the GitLab website, say foobar.

Then one could have executed the following commands on the command line.

mkdir foobar
cd foobar
touch .gitignore
git init
echo "# foobar repo created by hand" > README.md
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin git@code.stanford.edu:naras/foobar.git
git push origin master

Here is the session on windows.

I can also check that this indeed worked on the GitLab website.

Note, however, that GitLab makes the repository private by default!
